<p>Illinois weather, with its severe winters and humid summers, demands specific material choices and construction techniques to ensure durability. Local building codes, often stricter in urban areas and for historical properties, require meticulous adherence. Logistical hurdles like material delivery, limited staging areas, and parking in dense Chicago neighborhoods also need careful planning. A seasoned contractor anticipates these issues, providing solutions that protect your investment.</p>

<h2>Common Homeowner Pitfalls to Avoid</h2>
